  6→//#region src/chat_models.ts
  7→/**
  8→* Deepseek chat model integration.
  9→*
 10→* The Deepseek API is compatible to the OpenAI API with some limitations.
 11→*
 12→* Setup:
 13→* Install `@langchain/deepseek` and set an environment variable named `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`.
 14→*
 15→* ```bash
 16→* npm install @langchain/deepseek
 17→* export DEEPSEEK_API_KEY="your-api-key"
 18→* ```
 19→*
 20→* ## [Constructor args](https://api.js.langchain.com/classes/_langchain_deepseek.ChatDeepSeek.html#constructor)
 21→*
 22→* ## [Runtime args](https://api.js.langchain.com/interfaces/_langchain_deepseek.ChatDeepSeekCallOptions.html)
 23→*
 24→* Runtime args can be passed as the second argument to any of the base runnable methods `.invoke`. `.stream`, `.batch`, etc.
 25→* They can also be passed via `.withConfig`, or the second arg in `.bindTools`, like shown in the examples below:
 26→*
 27→* ```typescript
 28→* // When calling `.withConfig`, call options should be passed via the first argument
 29→* const llmWithArgsBound = llm.withConfig({
 30→*   stop: ["\n"],
 31→*   tools: [...],
 32→* });
 33→*
 34→* // When calling `.bindTools`, call options should be passed via the second argument
 35→* const llmWithTools = llm.bindTools(
 36→*   [...],
 37→*   {
 38→*     tool_choice: "auto",
 39→*   }
 40→* );
 41→* ```
 42→*
 43→* ## Examples
 44→*
 45→* <details open>
 46→* <summary><strong>Instantiate</strong></summary>
 47→*
 48→* ```typescript
 49→* import { ChatDeepSeek } from '@langchain/deepseek';
 50→*
 51→* const llm = new ChatDeepSeek({
 52→*   model: "deepseek-reasoner",
 53→*   temperature: 0,
 54→*   // other params...
 55→* });
 56→* ```
 57→* </details>
 58→*
 59→* <br />
